This MVEBU target is intended to be used on devices based on Marvell ArmadaXP/Armada37x/Armada38x ARM-compatible CPUs (aka PJ4x/PJ5x).

Following instruction were tested on Globalscape Mirabox v1.0 but should be applyable to other devices with minor modifications.
Device assumed to supports NAND.
Kernel resides in second partition (4MB) using uImage format.
Root filesystem resides third partition (1016MB) using UBIFS.

Currently only manual install/re-install procedure tested.
We use combined "factory" (kernel+rootfs) image called openwrt-15.05-mvebu-armada-370-mirabox-squashfs-firmware.bin we assue it's size to be 16MB at the most.

The following commands should be invoked from boot loader (uBoot) prompt.
(Remember to use apropriate network parameters)

1. Setup tftpserver with root at /home/tmp
2. Copy factory image to tftp server root
3. Prepare uBoot environment (modify network paramters if needed):
	>> resetenv; reset
	>> mainlineLinux yes; save; reset
	>> ipaddr 192.168.1.100; setenv serverip 192.168.1.4
	>> setenv loadaddr 0x2000000; setenv console 'console=ttyS0,115200 panic=10'
	>> setenv bootargs_root 'ubi.mtd=2'
	>> setenv rootpath '/home/tmp/'
	>> setenv image_name openwrt-15.05-mvebu-armada-370-mirabox-squashfs-firmware.bin
	>> setenv rootfs_name root
	>> setenv clean_mem 'mw ${loadaddr} 0x1000000'
	>> setenv flash_image 'run clean_mem; tftpboot ${loadaddr} ${rootpath}${image_name}; nand erase 0x400000 0x3fc00000; nand write.e ${loadaddr} 0x400000 0x1000000'
	>> setenv bootcmd 'run clean_mem; setenv bootargs ${console} ${bootargs_root}; nand read.e ${loadaddr} 0x400000 0x400000; bootm ${loadaddr}'
	>> save
3. Install openwrt:
	>> run flash_image
4. Boot into openwrt:
	>> boot

Good luck
